{"142": {"description": "The course entails substantial selected readings from the great Sanskirt epic poems--the Mahabharata and the Ramayana in translation, selected readings from the corpus of secondary literature on Indian epic studies as well as lectures on salient issues in both. Discussion will focus on a variety of historical and theoretical approaches to the study of the poems and their extraordinary influence on Indian culture. Readings will be supplemented with selected showings of popular cinematic and television versions of the epics. ", "displayName": "SASIAN 142", "sections": [{"enrolled": 25, "id": 32958, "number": "001", "status": {"description": "Open", "code": "O"}, "meetings": [{"instructors": [{"role": "1-TIC", "name": "Robert P Goldman"}], "location": {"description": "Valley Life Sciences 2040", "code": "VLSB2040"}, "startTime": "11:00:00", "dayAbbrvs": "MoWeFr", "days": {"Sunday": false, "Friday": true, "Monday": true, "Saturday": false, "Tuesday": false, "Wednesday": true, "Thursday": false}, "endTime": "11:59:00"}], "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "waitlistCapacity": 35, "type": "LEC", "primary": true, "enrollCapacity": 120, "waitlisted": 0}], "meetings": [{"instructors": [{"role": "1-TIC", "name": "Robert P Goldman"}], "location": {"description": "Valley Life Sciences 2040", "code": "VLSB2040"}, "startTime": "11:00:00", "dayAbbrvs": "MoWeFr", "days": {"Sunday": false, "Friday": true, "Monday": true, "Saturday": false, "Tuesday": false, "Wednesday": true, "Thursday": false}, "endTime": "11:59:00"}], "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "id": 32958, "title": "India's Great Epics", "units": {"value": {"units": 4.0}, "type": "fixed"}}, "1B": {"description": "This course offers a broad historical and cultural survey of the civilizations of the Indian subcontinent from the 12th century to partition of India in 1947. Attention will be paid to the geography and ethnography of the region, its political history, and the religious, philosophical, literary, and artistic movements that have shaped it and contributed to its development as a unique, diverse, and fascinating world civilization. Lectures, readings, and class discussions will center on salient texts, broadly defined, that have characterized major cultural, religious, and political formations from the medieval period to the 20th century. This course is open to all interested students and is required for those majoring or minoring in South Asian Studies. ", "displayName": "SASIAN 1B", "sections": [{"enrolled": 8, "id": 22339, "number": "001", "status": {"description": "Open", "code": "O"}, "meetings": [{"instructors": [{"role": "1-TIC", "name": "Munis D. Faruqui"}], "location": {"description": "Dwinelle 219", "code": "DWIN219"}, "startTime": "12:30:00", "dayAbbrvs": "TuTh", "days": {"Sunday": false, "Friday": false, "Monday": false, "Saturday": false, "Tuesday": true, "Wednesday": false, "Thursday": true}, "endTime": "13:59:00"}], "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "waitlistCapacity": 20, "type": "LEC", "primary": true, "enrollCapacity": 56, "waitlisted": 0}, {"enrolled": 5, "id": 22340, "number": "101", "status": {"description": "Open", "code": "O"}, "meetings": [{"instructors": [], "location": {"description": "Dwinelle 205", "code": "DWIN205"}, "startTime": "14:00:00", "dayAbbrvs": "Th", "days": {"Sunday": false, "Friday": false, "Monday": false, "Saturday": false, "Tuesday": false, "Wednesday": false, "Thursday": true}, "endTime": "14:59:00"}], "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "waitlistCapacity": 10, "type": "DIS", "primary": false, "enrollCapacity": 30, "waitlisted": 0}, {"enrolled": 3, "id": 22341, "number": "102", "status": {"description": "Open", "code": "O"}, "meetings": [{"instructors": [], "location": {"description": "Morgan 138", "code": "MORG138"}, "startTime": "14:00:00", "dayAbbrvs": "Fr", "days": {"Sunday": false, "Friday": true, "Monday": false, "Saturday": false, "Tuesday": false, "Wednesday": false, "Thursday": false}, "endTime": "14:59: